==English==
===Adverbial phrase===
'''''paulo post futurum'''''
#[[Eventually]].
#[[Sometime]] in the distant future, or possibly [[never]].
#*When a [[murder]] is in the '''''paulo-post-futurum''''' tense &mdash; not done, not even (according to modern [[purism]]) ''being'' done, but only ''going to be'' done &mdash; and a [[rumour]] of it comes to our ears, by all means let us treat it [[morally]]. &mdash;[[w:Thomas de Quincey|Thomas de Quincey]], ''Murder Considered as One of the Fine Arts''

====Synonyms====
*[[ad kalendas Graecas]]
*[[Real Soon Now]]
*[[when pigs fly]]

===Etymology===
[[w:Latin language|Latin]], "a little after the [[future]]"

